## ðŸ§¾ AI-Based Automatic Stationery Billing System

### ðŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project implements an **AI-powered vision-based billing system** that automatically detects and counts stationery items (eraser, scale, pencil, sharpener) from images or video frames, then **generates a formatted bill** with item counts and prices.

Built as part of **** course (CS-5031, Spring 2025), this project demonstrates the full pipeline of an applied computer vision solution: **data collection â†’ annotation â†’ model training â†’ GUI development â†’ real-time inference and billing.**

---

### ðŸ§  Core Features

* ðŸ“¸ Detects multiple stationery items in a single image or video frame
* ðŸ§® Counts quantities of each detected item
* ðŸ’° Calculates total bill using predefined prices
* ðŸ–¼ï¸ Annotates results (item name, confidence, price) directly on images or video frames
* ðŸ–¥ï¸ GUI application for user-friendly interaction

---

### ðŸ“ Dataset

* Collected a **custom dataset of 500+ images** of erasers, scales, pencils, and sharpeners
* Images taken in different combinations and backgrounds (some from  Images)
* Labeled using **** and saved in ** format**
* Split into:

  * `train/` (60%)
  * `val/` (20%)
  * `test/` (20%)
* Defined dataset structure in a `.yaml` configuration file

